name: tRNA (5-methylaminomethyl-2-thiouridylate)-methyltransferase
reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + tRNA containing 5-aminomethyl-2-thiouridine = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + tRNA containing 5-methylaminomethyl-2-thiouridylate [RN:R00601]
comment: This enzyme is specific for the terminal methyl group of 5-methylaminomethyl-2-thiouridylate.

references.title: Biosynthesis of 5-methylaminomethyl-2-thiouridylate. I. Isolation of a new tRNA-methylase specific for 5-methylaminomethyl-2-thiouridylate.
In: Salvatore, F., Borek, E., Zappia, V., Williams-Ashman, H.G. and Schlenk, F. (Eds.), The Biochemistry of Adenosylmethionine, Columbia University Press, New York, 1977, p. 251.
